msgid "cc_Alfar_description"
msgstr ""
"The cunning Alfars form a race as cruel and twisted as their homeland of "
"Nagast, located on the southern coast of Agon. As dark and unforgiving as "
"the bleak landscapes of their home, the Alfars relentlessly serve their "
"insane god-king Melek. Sleek and almost diminutive in stature, the Alfars "
"strike through their enemies like deadly, tenebrous maniacs, desecrating "
"their foes before vanishing into the darkness of night. Unlike the other "
"races, the Alfars neither have nor want any allies, seeking only dominion "
"over all and the fruition of their master’s twisted machinations."

msgid "cc_Alfar_faction_description"
msgstr ""
"Racial Perks:\r\n"
"Natural protections to magic damage. Durability bonus to crafted staves. "
"Mana bonus."

msgid "cc_Alfar_title"
msgstr "The Alfar of Nagast"

msgid "cc_Dwarf_description"
msgstr ""
"Excelling in all things techno-magical, the ancient wisdom of the Dwarves "
"dates back to the earliest days of Agon. This nation of stout warriors and "
"engineers follows the ancient teachings of the Mastersmith Ymir. In his "
"final days, he wrote a gargantuan book that covers each step the Dwarven "
"civilization should take over 10,000 years in order to elevate itself above "
"all others. Today, there is but one final chapter of this book for the "
"Dwarves to follow. The rock-hewn strength and earthen wisdom of the Dwarven "
"people is a combination that makes them truly formidable allies and "
"incredibly fearsome enemies."

msgid "cc_Dwarf_faction_description"
msgstr ""
"Racial Perks:\r\n"
"Active skill: Reduce stamina consumption. Crafted armor/weapon durability "
"bonus. Health bonus."

msgid "cc_Dwarf_title"
msgstr "The Dwarves of Dvergheim"

msgid "cc_Human_description"
msgstr ""
"Having the shortest life span of all the races, the Humans of Mercia are, by "
"nature, highly versatile and adaptive, and face each and every challenge "
"with fierce determination. Thriving in trade and all things mercantile, the "
"Mercians have built the most affluent and richest empire on Agon in a "
"relatively short period of time. Their home cities lie among the verdant "
"fields and forests of south-eastern Agon, among the ruins of the long lost "
"empire of Chaldea. Led by the magnanimous King Philip Malregard III, the "
"Humans are battle-hardened warriors hell-bent on shining the light of their "
"god, Auros, across all of Agon."

msgid "cc_Human_faction_description"
msgstr ""
"Racial Perks:\r\n"
"Increased duration of buffs/debuffs. Increased nourishment duration. Mana "
"bonus."

msgid "cc_Human_title"
msgstr "The Humans Of Mercia"

msgid "cc_Mahirim_description"
msgstr ""
"The wolf-like Mahirim combines the instincts of a natural hunter with an "
"astral spirituality that makes them a truly proud and formidable race. "
"Having flourished into civilization only fairly recently, these lupine "
"hunter-warriors built their society among the plains and steppes of "
"northwestern Agon, in a region known only as the Tribelands. The origins of "
"Mahirim society are shrouded in mystery and are a subject that most Mahirims "
"will react to with aggressivity. While truly imposing and impressive in "
"size, Mahirim hunters are swift and deadly combatants, and their preys are "
"almost always... too slow."

msgid "cc_Mahirim_faction_description"
msgstr ""
"Racial Perks:\r\n"
"Natural protections to melee and archery damage. Increased run speed. "
"Stamina Bonus."

msgid "cc_Mahirim_title"
msgstr "The Mahirim of the Tribelands"

msgid "cc_Mirdain_description"
msgstr ""
"The ancient Mirdains are a distinguished race of forest elves who reside "
"among the giant trees and sweeping valleys of south-western Agon. Highly "
"diplomatic and preferring subtlety to open warfare (except when armed "
"conflict is the only option), the Mirdains fight with an innate grace and "
"fluidity, moving through battle like a leaf in the wind and striking at "
"their enemies with surgical precision. The grace and marvelous beauty "
"characteristic of the Mirdains is matched only by their endless patience. "
"For them, a good plan executed immediately is prone to failure. Victory is "
"the perfect plan, executed at the perfect moment."

msgid "cc_Mirdain_faction_description"
msgstr ""
"Racial Perks:\r\n"
"Increased archery damage. Increased ID range. Stamina bonus."

msgid "cc_Mirdain_title"
msgstr "The Mirdain of Mirendil"

msgid "cc_Ork_description"
msgstr ""
"With bestial strength and a volatile temper unmatched by any other race, an "
"irate Ork is one of the most fearsome sights on Agon. With active volcanoes "
"to the north and putrid swamps to the south, the Orkish lands of Morak are a "
"perfect reflection of their natives; fiery and unforgiving. The Orks value "
"might above all, living in a constant state of war with the Humans and "
"Dwarves bordering their harsh homeland. The Orks worship Varaleska, the "
"Great Dragon, the most ancient dragon on Agon and also the mother of all "
"dragonkin. To the Orkish mind, might truly makes right... and the rest can "
"burn in the fires of the Great Dragon."

msgid "cc_Ork_faction_description"
msgstr ""
"Racial Perks:\r\n"
"Increased melee weapon damage. Increased weight capacity. Health bonus."

msgid "cc_Ork_title"
msgstr "The Orks of Morak"

